      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The complex issue of a state's de jure status raises questions about the International Law, particularly Article 93 of the Statute of the International Court of Justice. This article states that the delimitation of state boundaries is usually based on prior agreements or superpositions of territorial claims. If the original sovereignty wasn't officially dissolved, the Karyat Republic might be considered de jure to some extent, maintaining its sovereignty under conventional international law, but its sovereignty would have likely been effectively nullified due to external pressure.",
